Description: Fragment of oval handle and shoulder of a pottery transport amphora. Stamped at bottom of handle. Clay medium red-brown; hard fired. Ovoid stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 55, 35 or 110, 5 Name Elaitas -es- or -os; rare examples of the second are known, perhaps the ethnic from Elaia in Aeolis. From same die as an example in the Benaki Collection, Alexandria, but not clearly from the same die as 1925,0119.422.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1579)
